The '''Moheli bulbul''' ('''''Hypsipetes moheliensis''''') is a species of [[songbird]] in the [[bulbul]] family, Pycnonotidae. It is endemic to the Indian Ocean island of [[Mohéli]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s. Until 2011, it was classified as a subspecies of the [[Grand Comoro bulbul]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldbirdnames.org/updates/archives/species-2-0-2-11/|title=Species Version 2 « IOC World Bird List|website=www.worldbirdnames.org|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-30}}</ref> It is also considered a [[sister species]] to the [[Seychelles bulbul]].

